The paper deals with automated surface-anomaly detection using machine learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on deep-learning methods, which are a subset of machine learning and are often used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.LG (machine learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the design of the architecture and the required computational cost, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the creation of a dataset, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
